{
  "texts": [
    "While our work reveals vulnerabilities in visionlanguage models (VLMs), these findings must be interpreted in light of several constraints:",
    "Choice of VLMs: Due to computational constraints, we chose LLaVA and Qwen-VL for experimentation.",
    "Both are widely used, wellestablished models, yet other VLM architectures may exhibit different susceptibilities to jailbreaking.",
    "Our results encourage future research exploring a broader range of VLMs. 2.",
    "Limited Training Data Scale: Our dataset contains about 10K (image, text) pairs, with up to 92 poisoned samples."
  ]
}